		<div id="comment_body_64247362"><p><div class="quote"><p>They already know what needs to be done</p></div><p>This is false.  No one has so much as a novel idea about where to even begin.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>When it happens it won't be what people expect of AI though. It will be a computer that can pass as a human.</p></div><p>That is exactly what ordinary people think of when they think about AI.  It's a Hollywood cliche.</p><p><div class="quote"><p> And it will be incredibly dangerous. No "kill switch" is going to work because it will have already outmaneuvered its foes.</p></div><p>Speaking of tired old cliches...</p><p>You've confused science fiction with reality.  I'm going to guess you spend entirely too much time with the lesswrong cultists.</p></div>
	</div>

