		<div id="comment_body_64247092"><p><div class="quote"><p>The problem is people who use AI as weapons. We need effective defenses, not silly "kill switches"</p></div><p>The valid research question is: If you posit a rogue AI which can think several orders of magnitude faster than you and has reached a level of intelligence comparable or higher than you, it will likely be able to figure out ways around your effective defenses.</p><p>We know this is true in principle, because people who are slightly smarter (at least in a specific narrow field) than you regularly do that - hackers, penetration testers, etc. - so a hypothetical AI like that certainly will.</p></div>
